An NGO, Christian Rural and Urban Development Association of Nigeria (CRUDAN), has called for governmentsâ€™ collaboration with Civil Society Organisations (CSOs) in the provision of humanitarian services to disaster victims. The Programme Officer, South West of CRUDAN, Mr Anthony Fasheun, made the appeal in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Ibadan on Sunday. Mr Fasheun said such collaboration would go a long way in helping victims of disaster. He noted that CRUDAN had been providing humanitarian interventions for victims of disaster in all the regions of Nigeria since its establishment in 1990.